Foreigners Release Statements on Holiday of February 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- The chairman of the Mfumalanga Provincial Committee of the South African Communist Party who is provincial minister of Land and Agriculture and Dilip Barua, general secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist Party (Marxist�|Leninist) of Bangladesh, made public statements respectively on Feb. 10 and 9 on the occasion of the February holiday.
 They said in the statements that Kim Jong Il, the great leader of the Korean people, have comprehensively systematized and enriched the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung and formulated it as the guiding idea indicating the road ahead of the era with his energetic ideological and theoretical activities, and converted Korea into a powerful socialist country as it is. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They noted that the Korean people are dynamically advancing along the road of Juche, meeting all challenges of the imperialists even under the present complicated international situation, which is unthinkable without the outstanding Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il, an ever-victorious banner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The indomitable struggle of the heroic Korean people gives great confidence and courage to the progressive peoples of the world who aspire after a new just society free from exploitation, they said.

Joint National Meeting of KCU Organizations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- A joint national meeting of the Korean Children's Union organizations took place at the Pyongyang Indoor Stadium on Feb. 16 in celebration of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Present at the meeting were representatives of all provincial committees of the KCU, Children's Union members in Pyongyang and children joining in the KCU.
 Present on invitation were Secretaries of the C.C., the Workers' Party of Korea Choe Thae Bok and Kim Jung Rin, Minister of Education Kim Yong Jin, Chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee Ryang Man Gil, former anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, officials of educational institutions and press media and  senior party officials, youth league officials, war veterans and men of merited service in Pyongyang. 
 The meeting began with chorus "Song of General Kim Jong Il" and a congratulatory poem "Our holiday, joyful holiday" was recited.
 Then followed a ceremony of admission to the KCU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those schoolchildren joining in the KCU entered the venue of the meeting and solemnly made a pledge before the flag of the KCU at the call of former anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter Kim Ryong Yon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cadres, former anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, war veterans, youth league officials and men of merited service put red neckties around the necks of the affiliated children and pinned KCU badges  in congratulation of their admission on the greatest national holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The children made their first salute, responding with pleasure to the slogan "Let's always get ready for the respected General Kim Jong Il!" with loud chorus "Ready always!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then came congratulatory speeches by former anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter Ri Jong San, war veteran Ri Sang Ju, Doc. Jon Sung Guk, room chief of the Kim Chaek University of Technology, and people's sportswoman Kye Sun Hui, winner of the "Kim Il Sung Prize" and labor hero.

First Camping at Jangjasan Children's Union Camp
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Kanggye, February 16 (KCNA) -- The first camping of this year has started at the Jangjasan Children's Union Camp on the occasion of the significant holiday of February.
 At a ceremony of receiving campers a report was made by Jang Myong Ho, director of the camp, which was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said that the camp built on Mt. Jangja, a significant place associated with undying footprints leader  Kim Jong Il left during the past Fatherland Liberation War, is a good extracurricular educational base of the Children's Union members provided under the warm loving care of the Workers' Party of Korea.
 They called upon all the campers to deeply cherish loyalty to Kim Jong Il and firmly prepare themselves to be reliable pillars of the country who are knowledgeable, virtuous and healthy and thus carry out the cause of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Campers marched past at the end of the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were congratulated by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK, Choe Ki Ryong, chairman of the Jagang Provincial People's Committee, Kim In Nam, chairman of the Jagang Provincial Rural Economic Management Committee and others.

Art Troupe of Koreans in Japan Gives Guest Performance
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- The art troupe of Koreans in Japan celebrating February 16 gave a song and dance performance "For Leap Forward under Leadership of the General" for guests of honor at the Pyongyang Grand Theatre on Thursday. 
 Present on invitation were Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the DPRK Cabinet, officials concerned and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were delegations of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) including the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan headed by Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, and overseas compatriots on a visit to the socialist homeland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The art troupe consisting of dignified and talented artistes of the Kumgangsan Opera Troupe of Chongryon put colorful numbers on the stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers presented art works  praising the great man including mixed chorus "We Have Come to See the General", female vocal solo "February Is Spring", narration and song "We Believe in You as in Heaven" and female duet "A Cuckoo on a Road to the Front" carrying the best wishes of the 700,000 compatriots in Japan for Kim Jong Il whom they believe and follow even in an alien land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers were warmly acclaimed by the audience for successfully representing the features of Koreans in Japan steadily following the road of patriotism in male solo "For the Only One Country" and  "Let's Live for Morrow", mixed duet "In the Morning for Start" and female trio "We Love Our School." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance closed with mixed chorus "Let's Chongryon Advance under the Leadership of the General."

Celebration Concert Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 17 (KCNA) -- Artistes of the National Symphony Orchestra gave a concert celebrating February 16, birthday of leader Kim Jong Il, at the People's Palace of Culture on Thursday.
 The concert was appreciated by Pak Pong Ju, Ri Yong Mu, Yang Hyong Sop and others.
 Present on invitation were diplomatic envoys of different countries and members of the military attaches' corps in Pyongyang, members of the central military band of the Defence Ministry of Russia and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage were the fourth movement symphony "Glory to General Kim Jong Il" of the symphonic suite "Long Journey for Songun Leadership," male bass solo  "Korea, I Will Glorify Thee" and female soprano solo "Wellbeing of the Dear Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Is Our Happiness." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang of the undying feats of Kim Jong Il who has opened the heyday of prosperity in this land, glorifying the sacred annals of the Korean revolution as ever-victorious history with his great Songun leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Arirang" and "Rich Harvest Comes to the Chongsan Plain," mixed orchestral pieces with strong national character, touched the heartstring of the audience for reflecting the socialist reality full of national sentiment, optimism and joy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers showed well the features of the efflorescing symphony of the DPRK by playing famous music of other countries.
